Halong Bay - spectacular scenery
Jul 2012 ‚Ä¢ Couples
We booked a tour of 2 days 1 night to Halong Bay with halongsapa tours com. and it was the highlight of our tour in Vietnam. Ms. Cham and her husband Mr. Tien the owners of this travel agency offer various types of tours in very competitive prices to the bay. We took their advice to spend the night on the boat and it was wonderful.
We were on the Clypso junk and we had a cabin with a very large window. We could lie in bed and enjoy the spectacular scenery of the bay - the limestone hills and the calm emerald sea - through the window.
The food on the junk was excellent and the dishes were served in an artistic way.
The cruise package includes four hours on shuttle bus from and back to Hanoi, caving, a visit to a fishing village and kayaking in beautiful lagoons. We highly recommend to spend the night on the boat; enjoy the sunset on the upper deck while the boat is sailing silently between the limestone rocks and wake up in the morning in the middle of the breathtaking scenery of Halong Bay.
Unfortunately, there is no place in the TripAdvisor to write a review about travel agents, because traveling with a good-professional agency like Halongsapa tour (we booked 4 tours with them) makes all the difference!
Written September 8, 2012
kuleninevi
bucks18 contributions
Halong Bay with Vega Travel
We opted for the 2 day/1 night tour and booked with Vega as it seemed to have god reviews for a reasonable price. We upgraded to the de luxe cabin which was significantly larger than the others and had a balcony. The pick up was very prompt, the journey to Halong Bay tedious with the obligatory stop at a rip off tourist place. We were apprehensive about the boat having read some horrific reviews but we were pleasantly surprised, clean and comfortable. The balcony in our deluxe cabin, however was not a great deal of use, the sun blazed down on it all day making it impossible to sit out on, however keeping the door to it open allowed a draught through. One issue was that, whereas the other cabins had a proper door to the bathroom our room had a shower curtain across, which wasn't great and a real pain was that we were kicked out of the room at 9.30 the next day so it could be cleaned for the next guests so not sure the extra money was worth it for the de luxe cabin. The food on board was very good, one surprise was the very reasonable cost of the drinks, there was no price list so we kept our consumption down and expected the worst which didn't happen. Vega's itenerary is that you have lunch on the second day at a local restaurant rather than mid morning on the boat. The lunch was adequate though the soup was tasteless. One issue with the boat was the lack of sunbeds, 6 workable ones for 13 people. Halong Bay itself was lovely, it wasn't covered in litter as expected nor was it like Piccadilly Circus, though maybe that was just the route followed by Vega. One thing Vega really did get right was the timing of visits, we were the only group in the cave, brilliant and the only group kayaking in the lagoon, beautiful, plus we were the first group up Titop Hill so had that to ourselves, (be very aware of the mosquitoes there, most of us were bitten to death and the guide never mentioned thre might be a problem, in fact when I said he could have told us to put on mosquito spray his reply was 'that's the surprise' - which went down like a lead balloon) We were on the boat for 24 hours, which was as expected, with 2 x 4 hours slow, bumpy transfers, again expected. So although there were some issues, overall the trip was very good and good value for money.
Written July 14, 2012
jellyfur
Glasgow, UK40 contributions
Galaxy Cruises - FANTASTIC tour of Halong Bay
Jun 2012 ‚Ä¢ Couples
My boyfriend and I have just returned from a 3 day / 2 night cruise on Halong Bay with Galaxy Cruises and cannot recommend them highly enough.
When we got to Hanoi and started researching tour options, we immediately started to feel a little overwhelmed - there was simply so many cruise companies, itinerary's and options to choose from and all with drastically varying prices. Our hotel in Hanoi had several brochures but recommended Galaxy as one of the best options so we booked on their recommendation.
First impressions of Galaxy were good. The tour guide picked us up at our hotel in a nice A/C bus. The journey to Halong City was comfortable and nothing like the experiences other reviewers have commented on with their tour companies.
When we reached the boat I was pleasantly surprised. I wasn't expecting the rooms to look like the pictures in the brochure (they never do) but this was an exception. The rooms were lovely and clean with comfy beds and ocean views. The bathroom was modern and the shower good. The rooms also had A/C and a mini bar. The dining room and main lounging terrace were also nice and overall the boat had a good luxurious feel about it.
The food was outstanding and I mean outstanding! Plenty of fresh seafood (which was usually the star of the show) as well as other traditional Vietnamese chicken, pork and beef dishes. We couldn't believe the amount of food served and we left the cruise about a stone heavier. It was so worth it though as it was delicious!
Now onto Halong Bay itself...
Halong Bay is simply breathtaking and probably for us, the highlight of our time in Vietnam. We were lucky that the weather was good for the duration of our trip which made the scenery all the more beautiful. I'd seen lots of pictures of the bay before visiting but it was nothing compared to the real thing.
Our tour around Halong Bay was great fun too. We kayaked in and around the fishing villages, caves and lagoons, took a small trek up a hill for some amazing views of the bay and relaxed on the beach. We also visited the Pearl farm to cut open some oysters and look for pearls!
Each night when the boat docked we could jump from the boat and have a swim. It's worth noting that Galaxy anchor the boat in a less populated area of the bay where it's better for swimming as the water is cleaner - I saw a few reviews from other cruise companies where people got ill from swallowing some of the water but nobody on our tour had any issues.
Evenings were spent enjoying some drinks and murdering songs on the karaoke or trying in vain to catch some squid at the evening squid fishing.
Our tour guide 'Hoan' (nick name Happy) was lovely and made our trip even more special. He was really friendly and informative not only about Halong Bay, but Vietnam in general. We spend much of our lounging around time chatting to him and learning about Vietnamese customs and traditions.
I'd give Galaxy 10/10. I'd also recommend that you book the 3 day / 2 night cruise. It's a little more expensive but it's worth it as you get so much more time on the bay. Bear in mind that Halong Bay is 4 hours away from Hanoi which eats into your first and last day.
N.B. Galaxy Cruise's website is: http://www.halonggalaxycruise.com for users wishing to view info in advance of reaching Hanoi.
Written June 8, 2012
Katia E
