Trash floating everywhere, drug needles on the beaches
Apr 2012 ‚Ä¢ Family
I would recommend that all tourist boycott Halong Bay until the locals clean their mess. As some of the reviews here state, the water is so polluted it stinks. You do not want to swim there and even kayaking is nasty business as it will take you to a close encounter with all the waste that floats in the water. Plus all the cruises are over priced and do not offer value for money. All the activities are based on water (apart from the mandatory karaoke...) and you definately do not want to go near it.
Halong Bay is the biggest tourist rip-off of Vietnam. It provides livelihood and big money to such a large number of people that if the amount of visitors were to drop dramatically due to a protest movement I'm quite sure they would start cleaning the bay in a hurry.
